  "prompt": "I have a crush on a girl and do not have courage to propose to her. What should I do to tell her that I like her?",
  "response": "It's completely normal to feel nervous about expressing your feelings to someone you like. Here are some steps you can take to build your confidence and find the right way to tell her you like her:\n\n### 1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**\n   - Make sure that what you feel is genuine. Sometimes, infatuation can be mistaken for deeper feelings. Take some time to understand your emotions.\n\n### 2. **Get to Know Her Better**\n   - Spend more time with her, if possible. Engage in conversations and find common interests. The more you know about her, the more natural it will feel to express your feelings.\n\n### 3. **Build a Connection**\n   - Build a friendship first. A strong friendship can be a good foundation for any relationship. This also gives you more chances to understand if she might feel the same way.\n\n### 4. **Practice What You Want to Say**\n   - It might help to rehearse what you want to say. You don\u2019t have to memorize a script, but having an idea of your main points can make you feel more prepared.\n\n### 5. **Choose the Right Moment**\n   - Find a private and comfortable setting where you can have a conversation without interruptions. It could be after a fun outing or during a casual meet-up.\n\n### 6. **Be Direct and Honest**\n   - When you\u2019re ready, be straightforward about your feelings. You might say something like, \u201cI\u2019ve really enjoyed getting to know you, and I wanted to tell you that I\u2019ve developed feelings for you.\u201d\n\n### 7. **Be Prepared for Any Response**\n   - Remember, she might need time to process what you\u2019ve said or might not feel the same way. Respect her response and be prepared to continue the friendship, regardless of her answer.\n\n### 8. **Confidence Boosters**\n   - Dress in a way that makes you feel good about yourself. Engage in activities that boost your confidence. A positive self-image can make it easier to take the step.\n\n### 9. **Seek Support**\n   - Talk to friends or family members about your plan. They can offer advice and encouragement. Sometimes, just verbalizing your intentions can help reduce anxiety.\n\n### Example Scenario:\nYou could invite her for a coffee or a walk in the park, a relaxed setting where you feel comfortable. Start the conversation casually, then transition to your feelings by saying something like:\n\n\"Hey [Her Name], I've really enjoyed spending time with you and getting to know you better. I wanted to be honest with you and tell you that I've started to develop feelings for you. I understand if you need time to think about it, but I just wanted you to know where I stand.\"\n\nRemember, the most important thing is to respect her feelings and reactions. No matter the outcome, expressing your feelings can be a courageous and rewarding experience.",
